<paragraph blockId="4.[192,1440,1488,1929]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
The first species of the group was described from “ 
<collectingRegion box="[829,922,1489,1513]" country="Malaysia" name="Pulau Pinang" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Penang</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[932,1032,1488,1512]" name="Malaysia" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Malacca</collectingCountry>
” [West 
<collectingCountry box="[1123,1239,1488,1512]" name="Malaysia" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
], by 
<bibRefCitation author="Parry" box="[1290,1440,1488,1513]" firstAuthor="Parry" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" pagination="1 - 113" refId="ref6956" refString="Parry, F. J. S. 1864. A catalogue of lucanoid Coleoptera; with illustrations and descriptions of various new and interesting species. Transactions of the Entomological Society of London, Third Series 2: 1 - 113." type="book chapter" year="1864">Parry (1864)</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Parry" authorityYear="1864" box="[225,339,1520,1544]" class="Insecta" family="Lucanidae" genus="Nigidius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obesus">
<emphasis box="[225,339,1520,1544]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">N. obesus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[354,424,1520,1545]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="4.[192,275,1419,1441]" captionTargetBox="[228,1407,238,1367]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[213,1415,221,1373]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 2. Nigidius obesus Parry, lectotype male, with labels (inset)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3699467" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3699467/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
), and the species was subsequently illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Westwood" box="[1027,1238,1520,1545]" firstAuthor="Westwood" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" pagination="357 - 363" refId="ref7044" refString="Westwood, J. O. 1874. Illustrations of several additional species of Lucanidae in the collection of Major F. J. Sidney Parry. Transactions of the Entomological Society of London 1874 (3): 357 - 363." type="journal article" year="1874">Westwood (1874)</bibRefCitation>
. Since that time, most specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[458,570,1552,1576]" name="Malaysia" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[633,753,1552,1576]" name="Indonesia" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
in this group were identified as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Parry" authorityYear="1864" box="[1152,1267,1552,1576]" class="Insecta" family="Lucanidae" genus="Nigidius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obesus">
<emphasis box="[1152,1267,1552,1576]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">N. obesus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Gestro" box="[1284,1436,1553,1577]" firstAuthor="Gestro" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" pagination="303 - 340" refId="ref6741" refString="Gestro, R. 1881. Enumerazione dei lucanidi raccolti nell'Arcipelage Malese e nella Papuasia dai signori G. Doria, O. Beccari e L. M. D'Albertis. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naruraledi Genova 16: 303 - 340." type="journal article" year="1881">Gestro 1881</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Benesh" box="[192,350,1584,1608]" firstAuthor="Benesh" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" pagination="1 - 178" refId="ref6480" refString="Benesh, B. 1960. Lucanidea (sic). Coleopterorum Catalogus, Supplementa (Second Edition) 8: 1 - 178." type="journal article" year="1960">Benesh 1960</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bomans" box="[361,528,1585,1609]" firstAuthor="Bomans" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" pagination="137 - 152" refId="ref6562" refString="Bomans, H. E. 1991. Inventaire provisoire de Coleopteres Lucanidae de Thailande et description de trois nouvelles especes. (74 eme contribution a l'etude de Coleopteres Lucanides). Lambillionea 91 (2): 137 - 152." type="journal article" year="1991">Bomans 1991</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Mizunuma and Nagai" box="[538,872,1584,1609]" firstAuthor="Mizunuma" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" refId="ref6882" refString="Mizunuma, T., and S. Nagai. 1994. The Lucanid beetles of the world. Mushi-sha Iconographic series of Insects, Volume 1. H. Fujita Ed.; Tokyo, Japan. 1338 p." type="book" year="1994">Mizunuma and Nagai 1994</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Bomans and Benoit" box="[890,1210,1584,1609]" firstAuthor="Bomans" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" pagination="3 - 106" refId="ref6640" refString="Bomans, H. E., and P. Benoit. 2007. Inventaire provisoire commente des Coleopteres Lucanides d'Indonesie et de Malaisie. Lambillionea 107 Supplement 2: 3 - 106." type="journal article" year="2007">Bomans and Benoit (2007)</bibRefCitation>
gave an exceptionally wide distribution for 
<emphasis box="[502,625,1616,1640]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Parry" authorityYear="1864" box="[502,619,1616,1640]" class="Insecta" family="Lucanidae" genus="Nigidius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obesus">N. obesus</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
encompassing the range of all species in the group, as well as 
<collectingRegion box="[1381,1440,1617,1640]" country="Indonesia" name="Jawa Timur" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Java</collectingRegion>
and Sumba from which I have not seen specimens. 
<bibRefCitation author="Fujita" box="[827,987,1648,1673]" firstAuthor="Fujita" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" refId="ref6710" refString="Fujita, H. 2010. The lucanid beetles of the world. Mushi-Sha's iconographic series of insects, 6. Mushi- Sha; Tokyo, Japan. 472 p." type="book" year="2010">Fujita (2010)</bibRefCitation>
limited 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Parry" authorityYear="1864" box="[1091,1207,1648,1672]" class="Insecta" family="Lucanidae" genus="Nigidius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obesus">
<emphasis box="[1091,1207,1648,1672]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">N. obesus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[192,303,1680,1704]" name="Malaysia" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
and Sumatra and treated the Borneo specimens as an undescribed species. However, specimens from Sumatra and Borneo possess distinct male genitalia from those of 
<emphasis box="[1066,1189,1712,1736]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Parry" authorityYear="1864" box="[1066,1184,1712,1736]" class="Insecta" family="Lucanidae" genus="Nigidius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obesus">N. obesus</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and specimens from these areas can themselves be separated into two distinct species. The true 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Parry" authorityYear="1864" box="[1107,1221,1744,1768]" class="Insecta" family="Lucanidae" genus="Nigidius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obesus">
<emphasis box="[1107,1221,1744,1768]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">N. obesus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is thus far known only from peninsular 
<collectingCountry box="[452,564,1776,1800]" name="Malaysia" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
and shares the same gross morphology of the male genitalia as the other mainland Asian species in the group, 
<taxonomicName authority="Gravely" authorityName="Gravely" box="[653,889,1808,1832]" class="Insecta" family="Lucanidae" genus="Nigidius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dawnae">
<emphasis box="[653,784,1808,1832]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">N. dawnae</emphasis>
Gravely
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[905,1007,1808,1833]" captionStart="Figures 3–4" captionStartId="5.[192,287,1506,1528]" captionTargetBox="[215,1371,238,1443]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[203,1383,233,1453]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figures 3–4. Nigidius dawnae Gravely. 3) Major male, dorsal habitus. 4) Lectotype male with labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3699469" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3699469/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Fig. 3–4</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[192,1440,1488,1929]" lastBlockId="5.[192,1440,1572,1929]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="4" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
Specimens from Borneo and 
<collectingRegion box="[609,717,1841,1865]" country="Indonesia" name="Sumatera Utara" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Sumatra</collectingRegion>
share similarities in the overall male genitalic form but comprise two distinct species based on obvious differences in the pronotal punctation and the form of the anterolateral margin of the pronotum. In the Sumatran species, the punctation of the pronotum is more uniformly distributed and coarser. The pronota of the Borneo species (and both mainland Asian species) show clear subfoveate areas of coarse punctures juxtaposed with almost impunctate areas with only fine, shallow punctures, and the anterolateral marginal area is more strongly produced as well.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3699469" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3699469" box="[192,1315,1506,1528]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3699469/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" startId="5.[192,287,1506,1528]" targetBox="[215,1371,238,1443]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph blockId="5.[192,1315,1506,1528]" box="[192,1315,1506,1528]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,340,1506,1528]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Figures 3–4.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Gravely." authorityName="Gravely." box="[347,636,1506,1528]" class="Insecta" family="Lucanidae" genus="Nigidius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dawnae">
<emphasis box="[347,535,1506,1527]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Nigidius dawnae</emphasis>
Gravely.
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[642,665,1506,1528]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">3)</emphasis>
Major male, dorsal habitus. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[982,1005,1506,1528]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">4)</emphasis>
Lectotype male with labels.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="5.[192,1440,1572,1929]" lastBlockId="6.[192,1440,1566,1929]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="5" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">
While initially considering both species to be undescribed, I researched existing names that might pertain to these two Indonesian species. The Borneo species in the obesus group has not been previously named and it is described and illustrated (
<figureCitation box="[714,783,1738,1762]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="6.[192,275,1506,1528]" captionTargetBox="[223,1373,240,1459]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[210,1389,228,1476]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 5. Nigidius gravelyi Paulsen, n. sp., holotype male, with labels (inset)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3699471" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3699471/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
) below. The original description of 
<taxonomicName authority="Boileau" authorityName="Boileau" box="[1224,1440,1738,1762]" class="Insecta" family="Lucanidae" genus="Nigidius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helleri">
<emphasis box="[1224,1339,1738,1762]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">N. helleri</emphasis>
Boileau
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[201,269,1771,1795]" captionStart="Figures 6–7" captionStartId="7.[192,287,1471,1493]" captionTargetBox="[233,1354,216,1395]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[220,1364,210,1415]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figures 6–7. Nigidius helleri Boileau. 6) Major male, dorsal habitus. 7) Holotype male with labels. Photo courtesy of Antoine Mantilleri, MNHN." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3699473" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3699473/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
) from 
<collectingRegion box="[348,456,1772,1796]" country="Indonesia" name="Sumatera Utara" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Sumatra</collectingRegion>
mentioned its similarity to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Parry" authorityYear="1864" box="[790,904,1771,1795]" class="Insecta" family="Lucanidae" genus="Nigidius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obesus">
<emphasis box="[790,904,1771,1795]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">N. obesus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and, critically, the presence of a very prominent lobe on the head that is rounded anteriorly, truncate posteriorly, and perpendicular to the body (
<bibRefCitation author="Boileau" box="[200,366,1838,1862]" firstAuthor="Boileau" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="47 - 48" refId="ref6538" refString="Boileau, M. H. 1905. Description de Coleopteres nouveaux. Le Naturaliste 27 (431): 47 - 48." type="journal article" year="1905">Boileau 1905</bibRefCitation>
). This describes the lobed canthus of the obesus group perfectly. I requested an image of the 
<typeStatus box="[270,374,1871,1895]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[412,527,1871,1895]" class="Insecta" family="Lucanidae" genus="Nigidius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helleri">
<emphasis box="[412,527,1871,1895]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">N. helleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the 
<collectionCode box="[647,738,1872,1895]" country="France" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" name="Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">MNHN</collectionCode>
(
<figureCitation box="[755,826,1871,1895]" captionStart="Figures 6–7" captionStartId="7.[192,287,1471,1493]" captionTargetBox="[233,1354,216,1395]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[220,1364,210,1415]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figures 6–7. Nigidius helleri Boileau. 6) Major male, dorsal habitus. 7) Holotype male with labels. Photo courtesy of Antoine Mantilleri, MNHN." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3699473" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3699473/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
), which confirmed that it is the Sumatran species of the obesus group. This is surprising because the name 
<taxonomicName box="[913,1029,1904,1928]" class="Insecta" family="Lucanidae" genus="Nigidius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helleri">
<emphasis box="[913,1029,1904,1928]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">N. helleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been traditionally used for a Javan or Sumatran species of the cornutus species group that is present in most collections (
<bibRefCitation author="Mizunuma and Nagai" firstAuthor="Mizunuma" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" refId="ref6882" refString="Mizunuma, T., and S. Nagai. 1994. The Lucanid beetles of the world. Mushi-sha Iconographic series of Insects, Volume 1. H. Fujita Ed.; Tokyo, Japan. 1338 p." type="book" year="1994">Mizunuma and Nagai 1994</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Okuda" box="[400,552,1600,1624]" firstAuthor="Okuda" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" pagination="1 - 4" refId="ref6923" refString="Okuda, N. 2002. A new species of genus Nigidius MacLeay (Coleoptera, Lucanidae), from North Borneo, East Malaysia. Kogane 3: 1 - 4." type="journal article" year="2002">Okuda 2002</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Fujita" box="[564,709,1600,1624]" firstAuthor="Fujita" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" refId="ref6710" refString="Fujita, H. 2010. The lucanid beetles of the world. Mushi-Sha's iconographic series of insects, 6. Mushi- Sha; Tokyo, Japan. 472 p." type="book" year="2010">Fujita 2010</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3699471" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3699471" box="[192,1053,1506,1528]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3699471/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" startId="6.[192,275,1506,1528]" targetBox="[223,1373,240,1459]" targetPageId="6">
<paragraph blockId="6.[192,1053,1506,1528]" box="[192,1053,1506,1528]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,303,1506,1528]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Figure 5.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Paulsen" authorityName="Paulsen" authorityYear="2018" box="[309,597,1506,1528]" class="Insecta" family="Lucanidae" genus="Nigidius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gravelyi" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[309,499,1506,1527]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Nigidius gravelyi</emphasis>
Paulsen
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[608,669,1506,1527]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, holotype male, with labels (inset).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="6.[192,1440,1566,1929]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">
The second mainland species of this group is from 
<collectingCountry box="[880,1003,1634,1658]" name="Myanmar" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
, northern 
<collectingCountry box="[1138,1252,1634,1658]" name="Thailand" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Thailand</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[1325,1383,1634,1657]" name="Laos" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Laos</collectingCountry>
and was first described as 
<taxonomicName authority="Gravely (1915)" authorityName="Gravely" authorityYear="1915" box="[463,787,1667,1691]" class="Insecta" family="Lucanidae" genus="Nigidius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dawnae">
<emphasis box="[463,594,1667,1691]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">N. dawnae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Gravely" box="[602,787,1667,1691]" firstAuthor="Gravely" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" pagination="407 - 431" refId="ref6786" refString="Gravely, F. H. 1915. A catalogue of the Lucanidae in the collection of the Indian Museum. Records of the Indian Museum 9 (6): 407 - 431." type="journal article" year="1915">Gravely (1915)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Subsequently it has been identified incorrectly as 
<taxonomicName authority="de Lisle" authorityName="de Lisle" authorityYear="1974" class="Insecta" family="Lucanidae" genus="Nigidius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="larssoni">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">N. larssoni</emphasis>
de Lisle
</taxonomicName>
(de 
<bibRefCitation author="Lisle" box="[434,560,1701,1725]" firstAuthor="Lisle" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" pagination="785 - 804" refId="ref6821" refString="Lisle, M. O. de 1974. Troisieme note sur quelques Coleoptera Lucanidae nouveaux ou peu connus. Revue Suisse de Zoologie 80 (4): 785 - 804." type="journal article" year="1974">Lisle 1974</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Fujita" box="[570,709,1701,1725]" firstAuthor="Fujita" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" refId="ref6710" refString="Fujita, H. 2010. The lucanid beetles of the world. Mushi-Sha's iconographic series of insects, 6. Mushi- Sha; Tokyo, Japan. 472 p." type="book" year="2010">Fujita 2010</bibRefCitation>
) or 
<taxonomicName authority="(Mizunuma 2000)" baseAuthorityName="Mizunuma" baseAuthorityYear="2000" box="[752,1087,1701,1725]" class="Insecta" family="Lucanidae" genus="Nigidius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obesus">
<emphasis box="[752,865,1701,1725]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">N. obesus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Mizunuma" box="[879,1080,1701,1725]" firstAuthor="Mizunuma" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" refId="ref6854" refString="Mizunuma, T. 2000. Stag beetles II (Lucanidae). Endless Collection Series 5. Toshitsugu Endo; Tokyo, Japan. 101 p." type="book" year="2000">Mizunuma 2000</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Bomans" box="[1096,1276,1701,1725]" firstAuthor="Bomans" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" pagination="326 - 337" refId="ref6605" refString="Bomans, H. E. 1993. Notes diverses sur le genre Nigidius MacLeay et descriptions d'especes nouvelles (Coleoptera, Lucanidae). Lambillionea 93 (3): 326 - 337." type="journal article" year="1993">Bomans (1993)</bibRefCitation>
synonymized 
<taxonomicName authority="de Lisle" authorityName="de Lisle" authorityYear="1974" box="[192,432,1735,1759]" class="Insecta" family="Lucanidae" genus="Nigidius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="larssoni">
<emphasis box="[192,327,1735,1759]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">N. larssoni</emphasis>
de Lisle
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mizunuma" baseAuthorityYear="2000" box="[503,620,1735,1759]" class="Insecta" family="Lucanidae" genus="Nigidius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obesus">
<emphasis box="[503,620,1735,1759]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">N. obesus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Araya" box="[636,795,1735,1759]" firstAuthor="Araya" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" pagination="18 - 25" refId="ref6449" refString="Araya, K. 2003. Notes on some type specimens of the genus Nigidius from Asia stored in several European Museums. Gekkan Mushi 402: 18 - 25." type="journal article" year="2003">Araya (2003)</bibRefCitation>
included images of the type material for all three of these available names. 
<bibRefCitation author="Fujita" box="[482,642,1769,1793]" firstAuthor="Fujita" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" refId="ref6710" refString="Fujita, H. 2010. The lucanid beetles of the world. Mushi-Sha's iconographic series of insects, 6. Mushi- Sha; Tokyo, Japan. 472 p." type="book" year="2010">Fujita (2010)</bibRefCitation>
recalled 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Lisle" authorityYear="1974" box="[755,891,1769,1793]" class="Insecta" family="Lucanidae" genus="Nigidius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="larssoni">
<emphasis box="[755,891,1769,1793]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">N. larssoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from synonymy without mention of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Lucanidae" genus="Nigidius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dawnae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">N. dawnae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Examination of the 
<typeStatus box="[503,607,1803,1827]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">holotype</typeStatus>
from 
<collectionCode box="[680,762,1803,1827]" country="Denmark" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/mci8-ehqk" name="Zoological Museum, University of Copenhagen" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">ZMUC</collectionCode>
confirmed that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Lisle" authorityYear="1974" box="[959,1094,1802,1826]" class="Insecta" family="Lucanidae" genus="Nigidius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="larssoni">
<emphasis box="[959,1094,1802,1826]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">N. larssoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a synonym of 
<emphasis box="[1300,1440,1802,1826]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">
<taxonomicName box="[1300,1436,1802,1826]" class="Insecta" family="Lucanidae" genus="Nigidius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dawnae">N. dawnae</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Compared to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mizunuma" baseAuthorityYear="2000" box="[361,478,1836,1860]" class="Insecta" family="Lucanidae" genus="Nigidius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obesus">
<emphasis box="[361,478,1836,1860]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">N. obesus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the anterolateral pronotal projection is broader and more strongly produced in this species. When compared with similarly sized specimens, 
<taxonomicName box="[990,1123,1870,1894]" class="Insecta" family="Lucanidae" genus="Nigidius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dawnae">
<emphasis box="[990,1123,1870,1894]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">N. dawnae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the largest, broadest mandibles of any species in the obesus group.
</paragraph>
